 *1272556341*Singapore Observations
 - Area of Singapore: 707 km2, Tokyo wards: 622 km2
 - Singapore population: 5M, Tokyo wards: 9M
 - Buses come fairly often.
 - Surprisingly, there are cigarette butts. Some people walk around smoking.
 - There is an erotic goods store along the main street.
 - You can buy a Cisco router or an iPad at a shopping mall. It's like a big Akihabara.
 - There are plenty of trash cans.
 - There are plenty of smoking areas here and there, so it seems like a good place for smokers to spend some time.
 - It is chaotic and interesting to see four different languages mixed together. I can't read Tamil, so I wanted to learn it.
 - The management class is very smart. I feel that the country is being managed quite well. I thought that Japan should imitate them. I wonder if Japan as a whole is too big to use the same method.
